  • High-intensity statin first-line — rosuvastatin 20-40 or atorvastatin 40-80 — typically 40-50% LDL reduction;
  • Ezetimibe 10 mg add — additional 18-20% reduction; combination very effective;
  • PCSK9 inhibitors (alirocumab, evolocumab) — additional 50-60% reduction; SC q 2-4 wk; for FH + insufficient on statin/ezetimibe (esp ASCVD); high cost + insurance pre-auth;
  • Inclisiran (siRNA — Leqvio) — twice-yearly SC injection; emerging option;
  • Bempedoic acid alternative;
