(6) TIA/minor stroke acute medical:
  • Antiplatelet:
  • Aspirin 325 mg loading then 81 mg daily;
  • Dual antiplatelet (DAPT): ASA + clopidogrel × 21-90 days for minor stroke / high-risk TIA (CHANCE, POINT) then aspirin alone;
  • Aspirin + ticagrelor (THALES) alternative;
  • Statin high-intensity;
  • BP management: control but avoid acute aggressive lowering in acute stroke; target chronic < 130/80;
  • Glycemic control;

