  • Carotid stenosis > 70% symptomatic → CEA or CAS within 14 d;
  • AFib → anticoagulation (DOAC preferred);
  • PFO selected — closure for cryptogenic stroke;
  • Aortic / arch atherosclerosis — antiplatelet + statin;
  • Hypercoagulable — anticoagulation;

(8) Lifestyle modification + risk factor: smoking cessation, BP, DM, lipid, weight, exercise, diet (Mediterranean), alcohol;

(9) Patient + family education: stroke warning signs (BE FAST), call 911 immediately, no driving until cleared, secondary prevention adherence;

(10) Rehabilitation if deficits + cognitive evaluation;

(11) Mood screening + treatment — depression common post-stroke;

(12) Driving evaluation + return-to-work planning;

