Bell's palsy: peripheral CN VII (forehead involved). Rule out central, Lyme, Ramsay Hunt. Treatment within 72 h: prednisone 60 mg × 7 d → taper. Antiviral selected for severe. Eye care critical. Prognosis good — most recover. Refractory specialist. Multidisciplinary.

