Nutrition Science + Dietary Patterns Primary Care (AAFP + Dietary Guidelines 2020-2025):

(1) Dietary Patterns Approach (vs single nutrient) increasingly emphasized — DGA 2020-2025:
  • Mediterranean — strongest evidence CV, metabolic, cognitive, mortality (PREDIMED); plant-predominant, olive oil, fish, nuts, whole grains, moderate wine;
  • DASH — CV, BP (DASH-Sodium); similar to Mediterranean;
  • Plant-based — vegetarian / vegan / flexitarian; growing evidence;
  • Healthy US-style (DGA);
  • Low-carb / Mediterranean-low-carb / ketogenic — short-term weight + metabolic benefit; long-term data more limited;
  • Intermittent fasting — emerging; mixed evidence;
  • Whole food, minimally processed common theme — avoid ultra-processed (NOVA classification);

(2) Macronutrients (DGA 2020-2025):
  • Carbohydrate: 45-65% — whole grains, fiber, complex; limit added sugar (< 10% calories);
  • Protein: 10-35% — plant + lean animal + fish;
  • Fat: 20-35% — unsaturated (mono + poly — olive, avocado, nuts, fish); limit saturated (< 10% calories — red meat, full-fat dairy, butter); avoid trans (essentially banned);
  • Fiber: 25-38 g/d (most Americans < 50%);
  • Hydration: ~ 2-3 L/d total;

(3) Specific nutrient considerations:
  • Sodium: < 2300 mg/d (< 1500 high BP) — most Americans 3500+;
  • Calcium + vit D: bone + cancer protection; primarily food; supplements selective;
  • Iron: bioavailability heme > non-heme; pair with vit C;
  • B12: animal sources; supplement vegetarians + > 50 yo;
  • Folate: leafy green + fortified; pregnancy 400-800 mcg;
  • Omega-3 (EPA + DHA): fatty fish 2x/wk; ALA plant sources lower conversion; supplements selected;
  • Iodine: salt fortified, seafood;
  • Vit B-complex, antioxidants, magnesium, potassium, zinc — food preferred;

(4) Special populations:
  • Pregnancy + lactation: increased needs, folate, iron, DHA, calcium, vit D, choline; avoid alcohol, high mercury fish, raw, listeria-risk;
  • Infants: breast / formula + introduction solid 6 mo + iron-fortified + allergens early;
  • Children + adolescents: growth + development; calcium + vit D; limit added sugar / sugar-sweetened beverages;
  • Older adults: protein needs increase (1-1.2 g/kg); B12; vit D; calcium; address chewing + swallowing + appetite + social;
  • Athletes: macros + hydration + timing;
  • Chronic disease specific:
  • DM: carbohydrate management, glycemic index, Mediterranean / DASH;
  • CKD: protein moderate, K + phos as advances;
  • CV: Mediterranean + DASH;
  • HF: Na restriction + fluid;
