Documentation Efficiency + Burden Reduction (AAFP + AMA + ONC):

(1) EHR documentation = top driver of burnout + dissatisfaction; PCPs spend ~ 2 h documentation per 1 h direct patient care ('pajama time');

(2) 2021 E/M coding changes (CMS) — major win:
  • Documentation now based on MDM (Medical Decision-Making) OR total time (not bullet count of history + exam);
  • Reduces unnecessary documentation;
  • History + exam at clinically necessary level;
  • MDM elements: number/complexity of problems + data reviewed/ordered + risk of complications;
  • Total time includes pre-, intra-, post-visit on date of service;

(3) MDM levels for E/M codes:
  • 99202 / 99212 — straightforward: minimal problems + minimal data + minimal risk;
  • 99203 / 99213 — low complexity: 1-2 stable chronic, 1 acute uncomplicated;
  • 99204 / 99214 — moderate complexity: 1+ chronic with exacerbation OR 2+ stable chronic OR undiagnosed problem; data review; moderate risk (Rx management, MDM); MOST COMMON outpatient PCP code;
  • 99205 / 99215 — high complexity: severe exacerbation, multiple comorbidity, severe risk (escalation of Rx, hospitalization decision, drug toxicity);

(4) Time-based coding alternative when time > MDM threshold:
  • 99202: 15-29 min;
  • 99203: 30-44 min;
  • 99204: 45-59 min;
  • 99205: 60-74 min;
  • Prolonged services add-on codes (99417, G2212);
  • Includes documentation, chart review, results, calls, coordination on date;

(5) Add-on codes valuable to capture work beyond E/M:
  • G0444 / G0442 — screening (depression, alcohol);
  • 99490 / 99487 / G2058 — CCM (chronic care management);
  • 99495 / 99496 — TCM (transitional care management);
  • 99497 / 99498 — ACP (advance care planning);
  • 99484 / 99492-99494 — BHI / CoCM;
  • 99453 / 99454 / 99457 — RPM (remote patient monitoring);

(6) Strategies for efficient documentation:
  • SmartPhrases + templates for common conditions, but personalized + accurate;
  • Voice recognition (Dragon Medical, M*Modal);
  • Ambient AI scribes (Nuance DAX, Suki, Abridge, Heidi, others) — listen to encounter + draft note + orders + bill suggestions; major productivity boost + burnout reduction; growing rapidly;
  • Real human scribes (in-person or virtual) — alternative;
  • Team documentation — MA pre-charting + room prep + reconciliation;
  • Workflow optimization — pre-visit planning, room layout, EHR settings;
  • Concurrent vs delayed documentation — concurrent during/immediately after visit better;
  • Limit copy-forward — keeps notes lean + reduces errors;
